data.title: Iran backed Islamic Resistance claim another cruise missile attack on Israel's Haifa Port
data.meta_description: Witness the escalating tensions as Iraq's Islamic Resistance unleashes deadly 'Arqab' cruise missiles on a crucial Israeli port. Backed by Iran, militants claim responsibility for the bombings, signaling a volatile situation. In a series of strikes over the past four days, key Israeli locations have been targeted, including Mossad’s Glilot Intelligence Centre in Tel Aviv. The proximity of the strike to Kirya, where Israeli war cabinet meetings are held, adds to the gravity of the situation. Iraqi resistance issues a chilling warning, boasting of a bank of Israeli targets for future attacks, promising a relentless wave of unforeseen assaults.
